    • Method Detail

      • refreshBeforeExpiry

        public ClientCredentialsAccessTokenProvider.Builder3 refreshBeforeExpiry(long duration,
                                                                         TimeUnit unit)
        The access token is returned from AD with an expiry time. If you call get() within duration of the expiry time then a refresh of the access token will be performed. If this value is not set then the access token is refreshed on every call of get().
        Parameters:
        duration - duration before expiry time after which point a refresh will be run (on next authentication attempt)
        unit - time unit for the duration
        Returns:
        builder
